From c9d4dd147c30d56d6e39977d7fe968c1a08a606a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Zamil Majdy <zamil.majdy@agpt.co>
Date: Thu, 19 Mar 2026 21:18:29 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 01/13] feat(copilot): add tool/block capability filtering to
 AutoPilotBlock
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Introduces CopilotPermissions — a new model that lets callers restrict
which tools and blocks the AutoPilot/Copilot may use during execution.

CopilotPermissions model (copilot/permissions.py):
- tools + tools_exclude (blacklist by default, whitelist when False)
- blocks + blocks_exclude with flexible identifier support:
  - Full UUID, partial UUID (first 8 hex chars), or block name (case-insensitive)
- merged_with_parent() — recursion ceiling so children can only be
  more restrictive than their parent AutoPilotBlock
- apply_tool_permissions() — translates to ClaudeAgentOptions tool lists
- validate_tool_names() / validate_block_identifiers() — eager
  validation with actionable error messages

AutoPilotBlock input fields (4 new advanced fields):
- tools: list[str] + tools_exclude: bool (default blacklist)
- blocks: list[str] + blocks_exclude: bool (default blacklist)
Empty lists = no filtering (allow everything) — safe default.

Thread-through path:
AutoPilotBlock.run -> execute_copilot -> collect_copilot_response
-> stream_chat_completion_sdk (applies tool filter to SDK options)
-> run_block (checks block filter via contextvar)

Recursion inheritance:
_inherited_permissions contextvar stores parent ceiling; child
executions merge via effective-allowed-set intersection so sub-agents
can never expand what the parent allowed.

68 new tests covering all semantics, merging, validation, and block
test suite compatibility.
